alt=\"Register your pet\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; float: right;\"></strong></p>\n<p>If you have found a pet in DeKalb County with a registered rabies tag, you can look up the owner information online <a href=\"http://www.petdata.com/for-pet-owners/dkb/tagsearch\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>The DeKalb County animal ordinance requires all pet owners in DeKalb County to register their dogs and cats. Pet owners who do not comply may receive a citation and have to go to court. Pet license fees are:<strong><br></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Spayed or neutered animals:&nbsp; $10 for one year; $25 for three years (requires a 3 year rabies vaccination).</li>\n<li>Animals not spayed or neutered:&nbsp; $25 for one year; $60 for three years (requires a 3 year rabies vaccination).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>***Plus $10 late fee if more than 60 days overdue.</p>\n<p><strong>Pet registration can be done by mail or online: <br></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>By Mail</strong> - Please print and fill out this <a href=\"/images/DKB_Application.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Pet Registration Form</a> along with the correct registration fee and a copy of your pet's rabies vaccination certificate and send to:&nbsp; DeKalb County Animal Licensing, c/o PetData, PO Box 141929, Irving, TX 75014.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Online</strong> - Visit <a href=\"http://www.petdata.com/for-pet-owners/dkb/license-online\">http://www.petdata.com/for-pet-owners/dkb/license-online</a> to register your pet online.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For questions about&nbsp;pet licensing in DeKalb County, please call 1-877-835-6788 or visit <a href=\"http://www.petdata.com/for-pet-owners/dkb\">http://www.petdata.com/for-pet-owners/dkb</a>. While you are licensing your pet, we hope you will consider making a tax deductible donation to support LifeLine's lifesaving efforts in DeKalb County.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t </div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<div class=\"wrapper-footer clearfix\" style=\"height: 31px;\">\n\t\t\t    <footer id=\"footer\" class=\"footer sticky\" style=\"bottom: 0px; position: absolute; z-index: 1000;\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"footer-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"row\">\t\t<div class=\"moduletable\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n<div class=\"custom\">\n\t<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Copyright&nbsp;© 2015 LifeLine Animal Project Inc.&nbsp; All rights reserved.</span></div></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</footer>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/templates/js_impacto/js/jquery.innerfade.js\"></script>\n\t\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/templates/js_impacto/js/impacto.js\"></script>\n\t\t\n<script src=\"/templates/js_impacto/wright/js/utils.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n<script src=\"/templates/js_impacto/wright/js/stickyfooter.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n\n\n\t<div id=\"sbox-overlay\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"z-index: 65555; opacity: 0;\"></div><div id=\"sbox-window\" role=\"dialog\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"shadow\" style=\"z-index: 65557;\"><div id=\"sbox-content\" style=\"opacity: 0;\"></div><a id=\"sbox-btn-close\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"sbox-window\"></a></div></body>"}
